<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-12-04T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-12-04T15:00:00-05:00" n="387" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d387">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Commission/603: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_WHR1" type="from">Wilson</persName>) to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-12-04T21:00:00+01:00">December 4, 1932—9
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 4—5:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>55. From <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_DNH1">Davis</persName> and
                                <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_WHR1">Wilson</persName>. Please see
                            final paragraph 50, November 25, 9 p.m. We have discussed the suggestion
                            with <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_MMGFR1">McCoy</persName> and think
                            it is well to let you know that he feels rather strongly that there
                            would be an impropriety in his acting on a committee to find a solution
                            after <pb facs="0482" n="384" xml:id="pg_384"/> he had been a member of
                            a commission which had rendered judgment on the case.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_WHR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>